88
00:09:38,632 --> 00:09:41,012
Lin Tuo, hurry up.

89
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:45,300
Xiao Lu.

90
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:50,700
Can you help me make a cup of coffee? I have something to deal with.

91
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:54,400
You're so tolerant. You've been at the company for so long, and the product has been launched,

92
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:57,400
and you're still making him lattes every day.

93
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,200
That's what an assistant does.

94
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,400
Why are you still an assistant?

95
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,800
Being an assistant is pretty good. Less pressure.

96
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:07,600
Help me out. Extra sugar and milk, you know.

97
00:10:13,410 --> 00:10:15,900
   

98
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:18,600
Off work now. What shall we eat?

99
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:23,000
But, no noodles or dumplings. Let's try other dishes.

100
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,100
You know it. I have something to tell you about He Xindi.

101
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,500
I think she's been acting very unusual lately.

102
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,400
She seems overly concerned for me.

103
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:35,000
You know she's been pursuing the senior, right? But the senior ignored her.

104
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,500
Recently, she suddenly started to take an interest in me.

105
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:41,000
She told me today she wants to manage my money.

106
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,400
I said then you might as well provide for me.

107
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,100
Let's go.

108
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:50,200
My right hand is failing.

109
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,800
I said

110
00:10:58,612 --> 00:11:01,292
I can't move my right hand.

111
00:11:04,952 --> 00:11:06,784
What do you mean?

112
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,720
It's deteriorating.

113
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:17,520
   

114
00:11:36,752 --> 00:11:38,772
Xiao Que, I'll leave now.

115
00:11:38,772 --> 00:11:43,740
A'Bao. Sorry, do you have plans tonight?

116
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:45,412
No, nothing.

117
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,472
Perfect.

118
00:11:50,472 --> 00:11:54,692
Anyone who looks at it would think it's an arm issue. It won't raise any suspicions.

119
00:11:54,692 --> 00:11:59,172
Trust me. I have experience. One year in Junior High, I dodged my holiday homework with this trick.

120
00:11:59,172 --> 00:12:01,940
This counts as making good use of waste.

121
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:05,025
You're using it again. Nice.

122
00:12:08,652 --> 00:12:13,952
An arm injury would take at least three months to heal. It would work for at least three months.

123
00:12:13,952 --> 00:12:17,240
It takes 100 days to heal. Three months are reasonable.

124
00:12:17,892 --> 00:12:20,432
What if after three months?

125
00:12:23,068 --> 00:12:26,172
What if my left hand also fails?

126
00:12:26,176 --> 00:12:29,032
We'll put a brace on the left hand too.

127
00:12:29,032 --> 00:12:31,652
Don't worry. I always have a way.

128
00:12:38,396 --> 00:12:41,692
That's good. You really can't tell.

129
00:12:41,692 --> 00:12:43,992
I'll wear it when I go out.

130
00:12:48,792 --> 00:12:50,980
I'm thinking...

131
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:54,748
maybe you shouldn't work anymore.

132
00:12:54,748 --> 00:12:58,852
I have savings, too. And I also asked for some money from my mom a few days ago.

133
00:12:58,852 --> 00:13:01,612
My funds aren't profitable. I want to sell them.

134
00:13:01,612 --> 00:13:05,152
Then I'll have tens of thousands yuan. It's enough.

135
00:13:07,196 --> 00:13:12,924
If I don't go to work, I'll have no social security and health insurance.

136
00:13:12,924 --> 00:13:17,092
For medical care and medication, there will be a lot of expenses.

137
00:13:17,092 --> 00:13:20,272
The money you have won't be enough.

138
00:13:20,272 --> 00:13:22,710
I will earn more.

139
00:13:23,352 --> 00:13:26,332
He Xindi and I can make money through our live stream.

140
00:13:26,332 --> 00:13:29,492
If you don't work, we can pay the social security ourselves.

141
00:13:29,492 --> 00:13:31,972
And think about it. Your right hand is bandaged now.

142
00:13:31,972 --> 00:13:36,572
You can't draw designs with your left hand. It's not realistic to work like this.

143
00:13:36,572 --> 00:13:38,332
Right?

144
00:13:40,284 --> 00:13:42,212
I still don't understand.

145
00:13:42,212 --> 00:13:46,572
We haven't done anything wrong. Why the secrecy?

146
00:13:48,312 --> 00:13:50,552
They must not know.

147
00:13:55,152 --> 00:13:58,312
You hid it from Xiao Que.

148
00:13:58,312 --> 00:14:01,012
But what about your parents?

149
00:14:02,272 --> 00:14:04,432
It's not necessary.

150
00:14:04,432 --> 00:14:07,352
We can all think of a solution together.

151
00:14:07,352 --> 00:14:08,752
There's always a way.

152
00:14:08,752 --> 00:14:13,052
More minds would be better than just the two of us worrying about these things.

153
00:14:14,952 --> 00:14:18,752
This illness is not a cold or a fever.

154
00:14:18,752 --> 00:14:23,312
It's not something you can hide and recover from in a few days.

155
00:14:25,212 --> 00:14:29,632
Do you really... Do you really want to wait

156
00:14:31,232 --> 00:14:36,092
until you can't move at all before you tell them?

157
00:14:37,552 --> 00:14:43,220
Have you thought about how they'd cope

158
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:46,670
without being prepared?

159
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:52,500
Ever since that day, I've been worried.

160
00:14:54,292 --> 00:14:57,632
I can't even sleep.

161
00:14:57,632 --> 00:15:00,372
I'm just afraid that one day,

162
00:15:01,312 --> 00:15:04,752
if you fall down and can't get up,

163
00:15:04,752 --> 00:15:08,352
and I'm not there, what should we do?

164
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,040
Lin Tuo.

165
00:15:17,012 --> 00:15:19,632
Stop suffering alone.

166
00:15:28,072 --> 00:15:32,932
Hungry? Let's have hotpot. Let's go.

167
00:15:34,432 --> 00:15:37,832
You won't listen. Let's go.

168
00:15:37,832 --> 00:15:42,052
- What did you say? Say it again. 
 - Lower your voice. The neighbors are asleep.

169
00:15:42,052 --> 00:15:43,936
Your father is asleep too. Quiet.

170
00:15:43,936 --> 00:15:47,412
- What are you talking about? 
 - Lower your voice.

171
00:15:47,412 --> 00:15:51,452
Your father is asleep too. Come on.

172
00:15:51,452 --> 00:15:54,752
I understand that you wanted a drink, but why did you drag A'Bao along?

173
00:15:54,752 --> 00:15:57,172
You scared that kid.

174
00:15:57,172 --> 00:16:01,532
You kept saying you were fine, but you got drunk and threw up.

175
00:16:01,532 --> 00:16:04,032
- Fill it up for me. 
 - That's enough.

176
00:16:04,032 --> 00:16:07,372
- Fill it up. 
 - What are you yelling about?

177
00:16:07,372 --> 00:16:10,992
- Godfather, did we wake you? 
 - Dad, fill it up for my dad.

178
00:16:10,992 --> 00:16:14,572
- Godfather. 
 - Is she drunk? What? How did she get so drunk?

179
00:16:14,572 --> 00:16:16,392
Right, a company dinner.

180
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:19,132
- She drank too much. 
 - Didn't you drink?

181
00:16:19,132 --> 00:16:22,680
I did. I can hold my liquor better than she can.

182
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:26,032
She shouldn't be drunk like this. Look, her face is swollen from drinking.

183
00:16:26,032 --> 00:16:28,632
- Be careful. 
 - Just hold her.

184
00:16:28,632 --> 00:16:30,832
Dad, let me tell you.

185
00:16:30,832 --> 00:16:32,692
I'm an adult.

186
00:16:32,692 --> 00:16:36,924
I can survive without anyone. He's just Lin Tuo.

187
00:16:36,924 --> 00:16:41,632
Can't I live without him? Can't I go on living?

188
00:16:41,632 --> 00:16:44,492
She's drunk. Really drunk.

189
00:16:59,892 --> 00:17:03,931
Lin Tuo. What happened to your hand?

190
00:17:03,931 --> 00:17:06,852
I fell down when playing soccer. A fracture.

191
00:17:06,852 --> 00:17:09,032
A fracture?

192
00:17:09,032 --> 00:17:12,031
Right hand? How are you going to work?

193
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:14,231
It's fine.

194
00:17:14,231 --> 00:17:16,772
Okay, tell me if you need anything.

195
00:17:21,712 --> 00:17:23,892
What's wrong with your arm?

196
00:17:23,892 --> 00:17:25,752
I fell when playing soccer.

197
00:17:25,752 --> 00:17:30,252
How come you hurt your arm? Don't people usually hurt their legs?

198
00:17:30,252 --> 00:17:32,452
Lin Tuo.

199
00:17:32,452 --> 00:17:34,072
Chief Designer.

200
00:17:34,652 --> 00:17:36,492
Come out with me.

201
00:17:43,212 --> 00:17:48,132
Chief Designer is so cruel. He still has Lin Tuo work with his hand like this.

202
00:17:49,952 --> 00:17:51,992
What's going on?

203
00:17:51,992 --> 00:17:55,452
My right hand is failing. This is a camouflage.

204
00:17:55,452 --> 00:17:58,592
- You're quite resourceful. 
 - Are we going to a meeting?

205
00:17:58,592 --> 00:18:00,972
There's no meeting. Is work that important?

206
00:18:00,972 --> 00:18:03,032
I want you to see someone.

207
00:18:07,712 --> 00:18:09,412
Just come clean.

208
00:18:10,272 --> 00:18:11,812
About what?

209
00:18:11,812 --> 00:18:16,012
About what? Your break-up. As your father, I don't even know.

210
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:20,172
Do I deserve to be kept in the dark? Do I deserve to know nothing?

211
00:18:20,952 --> 00:18:23,632
Don't you already know everything?

212
00:18:23,632 --> 00:18:26,052
But you didn't tell me.

213
00:18:26,052 --> 00:18:27,472
She did tell you.

214
00:18:27,472 --> 00:18:29,492
When did she... When did she say it?

215
00:18:29,492 --> 00:18:32,072
Last night, when she was drunk.

216
00:18:34,292 --> 00:18:39,052
Even if you did tell me when you were drunk last night, still...

217
00:18:39,052 --> 00:18:43,652
He Xindi. She lied to me. Why did you conspire with her to deceive me?

218
00:18:43,652 --> 00:18:45,892
Aren't we on the same side?

219
00:18:45,892 --> 00:18:48,172
No, I didn't mean to.

220
00:18:48,172 --> 00:18:51,072
But she wouldn't let me tell you. I figured I couldn't be a traitor.

221
00:18:51,072 --> 00:18:54,532
Right now, in my heart, you are one.

222
00:18:54,532 --> 00:18:56,872
You can't do this to me.

223
00:18:56,872 --> 00:19:01,372
It's Lin Tuo who broke up with her, but I'm to blame for that. What did I do?

224
00:19:02,992 --> 00:19:06,952
Wait, what? Did Lin Tuo break up with her?

225
00:19:07,592 --> 00:19:09,092
No, I did.

226
00:19:09,092 --> 00:19:10,672
Why?

227
00:19:10,672 --> 00:19:13,052
I didn't want to be together.

228
00:19:14,992 --> 00:19:20,392
An Zhique. What are you playing at?

229
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:23,152
You have been fine. How can you break up just like that?

230
00:19:23,152 --> 00:19:26,060
You're not children playing house. You can't call things off like that.

231
00:19:26,060 --> 00:19:29,160
Most importantly, you've both met each other's parents.

232
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:33,752
If you break up, what should I... What should we do, right?

233
00:19:33,752 --> 00:19:37,132
Does meeting the parents mean we can't break up?

234
00:19:38,092 --> 00:19:39,912
An Zhique, you still think you're right.

235
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:43,072
Let me tell you, this... It's clearly your fault.

236
00:19:43,072 --> 00:19:46,280
I know Tuo well. He's such a good child.

237
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:51,012
I won't even mention how he usually treats us. He even paid for my surgery.

238
00:19:51,012 --> 00:19:54,932
He took on a huge responsibility at a young age. This isn't about the money. What does it show?

239
00:19:54,932 --> 00:19:58,532
It shows that he is responsible and accountable. Isn't that so?

240
00:19:58,532 --> 00:20:01,292
You can't find such a person easily. So why would you break up with him?

241
00:20:01,292 --> 00:20:04,572
You're making the wrong choice.

242
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:09,852
Are you saying that we can't break up just because he paid for your surgery?

243
00:20:09,852 --> 00:20:13,210
Does that mean I have to marry him?

244
00:20:13,772 --> 00:20:15,707
What's wrong with that?

245
00:20:15,707 --> 00:20:18,432
In the past, girls sold themselves to bury their fathers. I didn't even ask you to bury me.

246
00:20:18,432 --> 00:20:21,832
Why can't you make it work with him?

247
00:20:25,292 --> 00:20:28,256
He Xindi, stand up.

