00:20:28,256 --> 00:20:30,784
Tell me the truth. Why is she behaving so outrageously?

249
00:20:30,784 --> 00:20:34,292
I don't know. I really don't know. This has nothing to do with me at all.

250
00:20:34,292 --> 00:20:37,532
I still don't know what's going on. I swear.

251
00:20:37,532 --> 00:20:40,972
If I lie to you, I'll never make money through my livestream.

252
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:44,912
Fine, An Zhique, you say it.

253
00:20:55,772 --> 00:21:00,332
What is there to say? There's nothing to say.

254
00:21:00,332 --> 00:21:04,232
I'm telling you both. Neither of you should go to Lin Tuo.

255
00:21:04,232 --> 00:21:07,332
If you do, I will turn against you.

256
00:21:08,486 --> 00:21:10,447
- Xiao Que. 
 - Let her go.

257
00:21:10,447 --> 00:21:14,217
You're turning against me, aren't you? You're heartless for saying that.

258
00:21:14,217 --> 00:21:17,460
An Zhique, if you're capable, spend the rest of your life in your room and don't come out.

259
00:21:17,460 --> 00:21:19,292
Don't get married.

260
00:21:19,292 --> 00:21:21,392
I'm so angry. So angry.

261
00:21:21,392 --> 00:21:23,632
She's doing this on purpose.

262
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:31,160
These are the people who use knowledge to change the world.

263
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:35,700
Every time they develop a new drug, they save thousands or even millions of lives.

264
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:40,800
Compared to them, our professions seem somewhat insignificant.

265
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,300
That's what my father thought.

266
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:48,500
So he believes that if I'm not a doctor, I'm not in a proper career.

267
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:52,300
That's not necessarily the case. Every job has its value.

268
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:56,700
However, the value of some jobs indeed cannot be measured in money.

269
00:21:56,700 --> 00:22:02,000
I've never been to college. So I have great admiration for highly educated people.

270
00:22:05,700 --> 00:22:08,500
- Haiyang. Sorry for the wait. 
- Dr. Wu.

271
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,900
The meeting took longer than I thought.

272
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,400
No, sorry to interrupt.

273
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:14,900
Lin Tuo, this is Dr. Wu Xinrui. Dr. Wu, this is Lin Tuo.

274
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:17,400
- Hello, Dr. Wu. 
 - Xiao Lin.

275
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,500
- Nice to meet you. 
 - Nice to meet you.

276
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:21,700
- Have a seat. 
 - Okay. Sit.

277
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,000
You're so young.

278
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:28,600
23 years old.

279
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:33,000
Have you been diagnosed with ALS?

280
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,600
Yes, I have.

281
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:39,900
The doctor has explained some of the situation. But I personally really want to know,

282
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:45,600
from the perspective of your pharmaceutical research, are there any drugs against ALS?

283
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:53,800
ALS is indeed a project our lab has been working on.

284
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:59,900
But unfortunately, up to now, there is no cure.

285
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:05,900
Actually, the doctor has also told me there is no cure.

286
00:23:08,912 --> 00:23:11,092
But you do have a research topic.

287
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:17,400
Well... The development of drugs is a very complex and lengthy process.

288
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:20,100
It requires a significant amount of human and financial resources.

289
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:24,200
We do have a project on it. However,...

290
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:27,700
- the difficulties are tremendous. 
 - You need a lot of money.

291
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:30,400
Money is just a part. Of course,

292
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:34,000
with an investment, the project can be advanced.

293
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:37,700
But it might take ten years, decades,

294
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:41,500
or even the effort of several generations to complete.

295
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:48,900
You heard him just now. There is a project on ALS.

296
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,600
Dr. Wu's pharmaceutical company is researching it.

297
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:56,100
It's the same with many incurable diseases. Targeted drugs and specific cures have been developed bit by bit.

298
00:23:56,100 --> 00:24:00,300
In the past, dysentery was an incurable disease. Whooping cough could be fatal.

299
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:03,800
Smallpox and chickenpox were considered incurable, not to mention cancer later on.

300
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:06,700
Haven't they all been overcome one by one?

301
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:08,500
It's a matter of time.

302
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,800
Get in the car.

303
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:30,300
Do you know how much time I have with my illness?

304
00:24:33,412 --> 00:24:35,492
Three to five years.

305
00:24:36,952 --> 00:24:39,332
For me, time...

306
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:42,900
has a limit now.

307
00:24:44,412 --> 00:24:47,100
So what?

308
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:49,100
It's not tomorrow.

309
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:53,400
Three to five years is not a short time. Have some faith in yourself.

310
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:57,200
I am looking for experts and doctors in this field now.

311
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:00,800
Let's understand more about the situation, so we can have more options.

312
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:04,000
Didn't we learn a lot today?

313
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,200
Chief Designer, thank you.

314
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,400
There's nothing to thank me for.

315
00:25:19,572 --> 00:25:21,272
Child,

316
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:25,500
whose life has no limit?

317
00:25:26,252 --> 00:25:29,372
In the end, don't we all have to leave this world?

318
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,700
We can only move forward.

319
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:39,500
Moving forward.

320
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:45,100
Let's get a bite before returning to work.

321
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:47,200
Think about what to eat now.

322
00:25:48,132 --> 00:25:49,612
Okay.

323
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,200
Xiao Ye.

324
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:01,800
No matter what, you should still let your father know.

325
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,300
I don't want to go back.

326
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:12,700
So you're planning to go straight to university without even saying goodbye?

327
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:16,300
Eat. Let's talk after eating.

328
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:19,100
Dad. You always indulge him.

329
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:21,100
- I indulge him?
 - Of course, you do.

330
00:26:21,100 --> 00:26:23,800
He's always running over here on a whim. Why would you do that?

331
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,900
Going to university without saying goodbye?

332
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:29,000
The child doesn't come home. Don't you know what the problem is?

333
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,800
Both children don't come home.

334
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:35,100
Aren't you and Lin Shouzheng at fault?

335
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:38,400
I wasn't blaming you.

336
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:42,800
Xiao Tuo has been in Chongqing for such a long time. Have you ever visited?

337
00:26:43,500 --> 00:26:46,900
Xiao Ye has been with me for a semester.

338
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:49,540
Has Lin Shouzheng come by even once?

339
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:52,400
Why is it always the kids who are wilful?

340
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:55,600
If you ask me, Lin Shouzheng is the most wilful one.

341
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:58,700
Just tell him that. Xiao Ye is not leaving.

342
00:26:58,700 --> 00:27:02,700
He'll stay with me. Tomorrow, I will take him to university.

343
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:07,000
I'll pay the tuition fees. After all, what he's studying isn't something you like.

344
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,400
This university has nothing to do with you.

345
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:13,100
Come, go play gateball with me.

346
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,300
Dad, finish your meal first before...

347
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:19,000
I'm full. Take your time.

348
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,200
Seriously.

349
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:25,900
He's spoiled Xiao Ye.

350
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:30,000
Grandpa. Where will we play gateball this late?

351
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:32,100
There's no gateball.

352
00:27:32,100 --> 00:27:34,700
I didn't want to stay inside and argue with your mom.

353
00:27:34,700 --> 00:27:38,600
She's 50 years old. I feel bad if she gets upset.

354
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:42,200
- Are you really going to take me to university? 
 - Of course.

355
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:44,300
I might also check on your brother.

356
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:48,500
Lately, I've been feeling uneasy. I keep feeling like something has happened.

357
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,700
Did he have a fight with Xiao Que?

358
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:53,700
Impossible. They never fight.

359
00:27:54,472 --> 00:27:57,992
That's good. We're going to visit him.

360
00:27:57,992 --> 00:27:59,300
Okay, let's go.

361
00:27:59,300 --> 00:28:02,700
Let's each have an ice cream. Take a carefree stroll.

362
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:12,200
Don't delete his WeChat account. It'd be so awkward if they made up.

363
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:14,400
Can they really reconcile under these circumstances?

364
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:18,400
How long has it been? Just think about it. If Xiao Que really wanted to break up,

365
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,200
why would she get drunk?

366
00:28:20,812 --> 00:28:22,464
Let's wait and see.

367
00:28:23,072 --> 00:28:26,332
No need to wait. Just delete it.

368
00:28:26,332 --> 00:28:29,792
Let's get over it. We're not getting back together.

369
00:28:33,652 --> 00:28:35,232
Go to work.

370
00:28:57,200 --> 00:29:01,100
Guangpu. My grandpa is here.

371
00:29:02,300 --> 00:29:05,000
So suddenly? When did he arrive?

372
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,300
- Is it okay? 
 - Yes.

373
00:29:15,300 --> 00:29:17,900
I got a fracture when playing soccer, Don't get it wrong, got it?

374
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:23,100
I got it. The main problem is what if your grandpa asked about Xiao Que?

375
00:29:23,100 --> 00:29:25,100
We'll handle it later.

376
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,200
Xiao Ye.

377
00:29:45,652 --> 00:29:47,772
What happened to your arm?

378
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:52,100
I fell while playing soccer.

379
00:29:52,100 --> 00:29:54,300
You fell while playing soccer?

380
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,400
Xiao Que never mentioned it to me.

381
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,400
I didn't want you to worry.

382
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:06,600
Right, Grandpa. It's normal to fall when playing soccer.

383
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:10,300
Thank you for cooking so many dishes after a long ride. Wouldn't it be better to eat out?

384
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:13,900
Dinner will be ready in ten minutes. Take a seat to rest.

385
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:18,300
You make us feel worried. How could you hurt yourself like this?

386
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:30,300
Grandpa. You should tell us before you came.

387
00:30:30,300 --> 00:30:34,100
What else is there to say? I knew you were busy, so I didn't disturb you.

388
00:30:34,100 --> 00:30:37,300
Xiao Que just brought the two of us over.

389
00:30:37,300 --> 00:30:40,700
You could have just called, and I would have come to pick you up.

390
00:30:40,700 --> 00:30:44,900
No need. Do you think I'm so old that I can't walk anymore?

391
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:48,096
Does it hurt?

392
00:30:48,100 --> 00:30:50,600
It's all right. Let's dig in, Grandpa.

393
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:52,200
Let's dig in.

394
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:57,100
Wait a moment. We have another guest arriving soon.

395
00:30:58,500 --> 00:31:01,100
- Coming. 
 - I'll go get it.

396
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:05,900
- Uncle. Hello, Uncle. 
 - Xiao Chen is here too?

397
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:09,500
- Old An, you've come. 
 - Uncle, I'm here, Uncle.

398
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:12,000
- This isn't much. Of course, I should. 
 - You didn't have to.

399
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,000
- We are waiting for you. 
 - Thank you.

400
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,500
Come on. Sit down.

401
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:19,200
- Have a seat, and let's eat. 
 - Okay.

402
00:31:19,872 --> 00:31:23,400
- I'm not sure if it suits your taste. 
 - I like it.

403
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:25,100
What happened to your hand?

404
00:31:25,100 --> 00:31:27,900
He hurt himself when playing soccer.

405
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:30,000
Yes, Uncle.

406
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:34,000
That's quite normal. Now you can even chip a tooth while swimming.

407
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:39,100
He's so careless. Come on. Come on, try the dish and see if you like it.

408
00:31:39,100 --> 00:31:41,100
Come on. Let's eat.

409
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:42,700
Yeah.

410
00:31:57,820 --> 00:31:59,752
How come you're here?

411
00:32:04,316 --> 00:32:06,892
When did you fall?

412
00:32:08,188 --> 00:32:09,992
A couple of days ago.

413
00:32:11,008 --> 00:32:14,392
You seem to be in good spirits. You went to play soccer.

414
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,300
So, that's why I fell.

415
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:25,400
I didn't want Grandpa to feel upset. So I came.

416
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:30,800
Why is Uncle here too?

417
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:35,400
Well, Grandpa said he wanted to see my dad. I couldn't just say no.

418
00:32:38,464 --> 00:32:40,192
Well...

419
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:44,600
- Does your dad know it? 
 - He does.

420
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:51,400
Well... Why did he show up anyway?

421
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:55,700
My dad is a man who insists, unlike you.

422
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:03,500
What are you two chatting about, right next to the trash can?

423
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:04,800
Where are you going?

424
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:07,200
Going downstairs to buy some stuff.

425
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:09,300
Is your cafe close to here?

426
00:33:09,300 --> 00:33:11,300
Not far. I'll take you there for fun tomorrow.

427
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:13,000
Okay, it's settled then.

428
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:15,200
You have to work when you go.

429
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:18,000
- Then I won't go. 
 - How dare you?

430
00:33:24,900 --> 00:33:28,700
I've saved this tea set and tea leaves specially for you.

431
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:32,500
I heard from Xiao Que that you love tea. I remember that.

432
00:33:32,500 --> 00:33:34,400
You're considerate.

433
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:37,400
Have a try.

434
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:41,400
This tea smells so good.

435
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:44,200
Come on.

436
00:33:48,300 --> 00:33:50,000
That's great.

437
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:55,000
Xiao Tuo is lucky to meet Xiao Que.

438
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:58,200
And you too. You're a great father.

439
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:00,800
It's his double blessing.

440
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:07,400
Right now, I'm just anxious for them to get married soon

441
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:10,600
so that I can have a great-grandson.

442
00:34:13,900 --> 00:34:16,700
Yeah. I'm also looking forward to it.

443
00:34:16,700 --> 00:34:18,300
Isn't that so?

444
00:34:18,300 --> 00:34:20,400
Come on. Have some tea.

445
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:26,700
Uncle, please, you don't need to escort me out. Stay here for a few more days.

446
00:34:26,700 --> 00:34:29,200
I'll take you out for some fun. We can have tea.

447
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:31,200
- Take good care of yourself. 
 - All right.

448
00:34:31,200 --> 00:34:32,800
- I'll be waiting for you. 
 - Yeah. Of course.

449
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:35,200
Grandpa, come and visit our cafe with Xiao Ye later.

450
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:37,700
All right, I will. I want to visit it.

451
00:34:37,700 --> 00:34:39,700
- Okay, see you then. 
 - See you, Grandpa.

452
00:34:39,700 --> 00:34:41,600
- Goodbye, Grandpa. 
 - Take care.

453
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:44,300
- Goodbye, Uncle. 
 - Okay, bye.

454
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,400
Dad.

455
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:49,600
- You're going too far. 
 - Thank you.

456
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:52,000
- I forgot to give them the sausage. 
 - I'll do it.

457
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,200
- Seriously. 
 - I'm telling you, you should...

458
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:57,500
What's going on?

459
00:34:57,500 --> 00:35:00,200
She insists on drinking milk tea. Why would you want that?

460
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:03,200
- You'll get fat. You can't drink that. 
 - Yes, you will. You shouldn't.

461
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:05,100
- Sausages I filled. 
 - Thank you.

462
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:06,900
Steam before slicing, and it goes well with alcohol.

463
00:35:06,900 --> 00:35:10,000
- Thank you. I love sausages the most. Thank you. 
 - That's good to know. Great.

464
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:12,400
- All right. 
 - See you then.

465
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:15,400
- Goodbye, Grandpa. 
 - Okay.

466
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,600
Press that button.

467
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:23,560
You're the best.

468
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:53,300
Take this card. Spend it wisely.

469
00:35:53,300 --> 00:35:58,200
No need. Mom gave the tuition fees to Grandpa. And he also gave me living expenses.

470
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:01,700
I saved this money for you anyway.

471
00:36:03,900 --> 00:36:07,700
Take it. Keep it for yourself, and take care of yourself.

472
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,300
When does school start?

473
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:17,700
The registration is in three days.

474
00:36:19,164 --> 00:36:21,052
Three days?

475
00:36:21,772 --> 00:36:23,492
All right.

476
00:36:24,700 --> 00:36:27,000
Have you told Dad?

477
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:30,100
No.

478
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:34,200
He's been ignoring you?

479
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:43,600
He remains the same all the time.

480
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:48,200
All right, go to sleep.

481
00:36:48,200 --> 00:36:51,100
I'm going to sleep too. I have to work tomorrow.

